Former federal lawmaker, Shehu Sani, has advised the Nigerian Medical Association (NMA) to invite ahead of the 2023 general elections, all presidential candidates for a medical check up, owing to the controversies surrounding their health status. The call undoubtedly stems from the series of bad health allegations labeled on the candidates of the All Progressives Congress and Peoples Democratic Party, Bola Ahmed Tinubu and Atiku Abubakar respectively. READ ALSO: Shehu Sani Slams APC Of Plunging Nigerians Deeper Into Poverty The ex-Kaduna Central Senator, who made the call via his Twitter handle on Thursday, however stated that the results be made public after conducting the tests. The tweet read “The Nigerian Medical Association NMA and the Nurses Association NANNM, should invite all the Presidential candidates for a complete medical tests,and make the result public. “This will settle the controversy over the health status of the contenders.”  